; PaideiaOS IPC Phase-1 Smoke Test: Fill to Capacity
; P3-011b: Test ENQUEUE_FULL behavior when ring is saturated
; Design reference: design/ipc/phase1-api.md §6

module IpcSmokeFillFull

; Test: Fill channel to capacity, verify FULL error on overflow

; Constants
TEST_CHANNEL_CAPACITY = 4        ; Small capacity to saturate easily
TEST_SLOT_SIZE = 256
TEST_MESSAGE_SIZE = 32

; Expected outcomes:
; 1. ipc_create_channel(4, 256) succeeds
; 2. Loop: enqueue message i for i=0..3 — all succeed (ENQUEUE_OK)
; 3. Attempt enqueue on 4th message returns ENQUEUE_FULL
; 4. Dequeue one message — succeeds
; 5. Enqueue again — succeeds (slot freed)
; 6. Verify messages are FIFO ordered (dequeue order matches enqueue order)

; STUB: Constants and test outline only
; Runtime: Deferred to paideia-as Phase 7+

end module
